Summary
Perverts is Hayden Anhedönia’s 90-minute-long fourth extended play under the alias Ethel Cain, released on January 8, 2025. The record was fully produced and mixed by Hayden. The lead single, "Punish", was released on November 1, 2024. It is not related to the actual character of Ethel Cain that we learned about in 2022’s “Preacher’s Daughter”. Ethel Cain released her debut studio album, Preacher's Daughter, in 2022, to critical acclaim. It centered on the fictional character of the same name, and contained Southern Gothic imagery and themes including religious indoctrination, sexual violence, isolation, and family trauma.
